body.description: Keep lavatories fully stocked with this 48-pack of Coastwide Professional two-ply recycled standard bath tissue rolls. Reduce cross-contamination and ensure clean restrooms with these two-ply bath tissue rolls. The 100 percent recycled paper is whitened with a chlorine-free chemical treatment and is free of dyes and fragrances to be gentle on sensitive skin. These Coastwide Professional two-ply recycled standard bath tissue rolls have a two-ply construction that's absorbent and strong, and the individual wrapping keeps the rolls clean before use. 2-ply toilet paper contains 350 sheets per roll for long-lasting use. Fits standard roll holders/dispensers. No added dyes or fragrances, safe for use with sensitive skin. Contains 48 rolls per carton (350 sheets per roll) for an economical purchase. Comes in white. Environmentally friendly alternative made from 40% post-consumer recycled fiber. Contains 100% recycled content. Whitened without chlorine bleaching and does not have any additional dyes or fragrances; safe for use with sensitive skin. Each roll is individually wrapped to minimize the risk of contamination and promote a cleaner restroom experience. Meets or exceeds Green Seal standards.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 12, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Not the best product
reviews.reviewText: The price was lower than other paper products but the rolls themselves are poor quality. I have used coastwide before and this time I was a little taken back. The roll is to loosely rolled around the paper board and has a very Scott's Septic Safe Toilet texture, not ideal for a commercial property with lots of traffic.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 15, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great toilet paper for sensitive skin!
reviews.reviewText: Great toilet paper! Holds up well, not too soft or hard. And free of harmful chemicals ( as far as I know) I think it is also recycled material so they aren't wasting trees to make it. I can buy 80 rolls for a great price and it lasts my family of 7 for about 3 months! My favorite toilet paper! Hope they get it back in stock.
